.TH "snd_soc_runtime_ignore_pmdown_time" 9 "snd_soc_runtime_ignore_pmdown_time" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_runtime_ignore_pmdown_time \- Check whether to ignore the power down delay
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" snd_soc_runtime_ignore_pmdown_time
.BI "(struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rtd" 12
The ASoC PCM runtime that should be checked.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks whether the power down delay should be ignored for a
specific PCM runtime. Returns true if the delay is 0, if it the DAI link has
been configured to ignore the delay, or if none of the components benefits
from having the delay.
